# RaceWise (Paceline) - AI Ultramarathon Race Planning SaaS

## Project Overview
RaceWise is an AI-powered platform that transforms 30 hours of scattered ultramarathon race planning into a 10-minute automated process. We deliver personalized race-day execution guides that reduce pre-race anxiety and increase finish rates by 15%.

## Key Documentation
- **Full PRD:** `/docs/PRD_COMPLETE.md` - Complete product specifications
- **Quick Reference:** `/docs/QUICK_REFERENCE.md` - Key numbers and APIs
- **Claude Code Context:** `/.claude/CLAUDE.md` - Project context for Claude Code agent
- **Tasks:** `/.claude/tasks/` - Current development tasks
- **Decisions:** `/.claude/decisions/` - Architecture decision records

## Product Context

### Target User: Alex Chen
- Age 38, Software Engineer, Salt Lake City
- Training for Wasatch Front 100 (14 weeks away)
- Pain: "I don't have 30 hours to piece together a race plan"
- Fear: "I barely made mile 62 cutoff with 8 minutes to spare last race"
- Goal: Finish with 3+ hour cutoff buffer, organized crew support

### Core Value Proposition
- **Time:** 30 hours DIY → 10 minutes automated
- **Anxiety:** Overwhelming chaos → calm confidence  
- **Quality:** Strava-powered, elevation-adjusted pacing strategies
- **Comprehensive:** 8 sections (pacing, crew, nutrition, drop bags, cutoffs, weather, contingencies, mental)

### Pricing Tiers
- **Essential:** $29 (first-timers, basic planning)
- **Custom:** $99 ★ Most Popular (Strava integration, full personalization)
- **Ultra Bundle:** $497 (5 races, $99/race)

### Success Metrics (6 Months)
- 500 guides sold = $50,000 revenue
- <5% refund rate
- 8+/10 satisfaction score
- <5 minute AI generation time
- 15% finish rate improvement

## Tech Stack (From Starter Kit)

### Core Framework
- **Next.js:** 15.3.1 with App Router
- **TypeScript:** Strict mode enabled
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui components
- **Deployment:** Vercel (zero-config)

### Database & Auth
- **Database:** Neon PostgreSQL (serverless, autoscaling)
- **ORM:** Drizzle ORM (type-safe queries)
- **Authentication:** Better Auth v1.2.8
  - Email/password + Google OAuth
  - Database-backed sessions
  - Built-in Polar.sh integration

### Payment & Subscriptions
- **Payment Provider:** Polar.sh
- **Products:** Essential ($29), Custom ($99), Ultra Bundle ($497)
- **Webhooks:** subscription.created, subscription.active, subscription.canceled

### AI & Generation
- **AI Provider:** OpenAI GPT-4 Turbo
- **Architecture:** 8-step agent cascade
- **Generation Time:** <5 minutes target
- **Cost:** ~$0.50-1.00 per guide

### File Storage & Email
- **PDF Generation:** Puppeteer (HTML → PDF)
- **Storage:** Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible, zero egress fees)
- **Email:** Resend (React email templates)

### Analytics
- **Analytics:** PostHog (product analytics, session replay)
- **Monitoring:** Vercel Analytics

## Database Schema

### Core Tables
```typescript
// Users (Better Auth managed)
users: id, email, name, image, createdAt, updatedAt

// Purchases
purchases: id, userId, tier, amount, polarSubscriptionId, status, createdAt

// Questionnaires
questionnaires: id, purchaseId, raceName, raceDate, goalFinishTime, 
  stravaAthleteId, stravaData (jsonb), nutritionPreferences (jsonb),
  recentRaceResults, biggestRaceFears, completedAt, createdAt

// Guides (Generated PDFs)
guides: id, purchaseId, questionnaireId, pdfUrl, sections (jsonb),
  generationTime, aiCost, createdAt

// Race Database
races: id, name, distance, elevationGain, location, website,
  courseProfile (jsonb), weatherPatterns (jsonb), createdAt

// Subscriptions (Ultra Bundle)
subscriptions: id, userId, polarSubscriptionId, status, 
  guidesRemaining, createdAt
```

## Key Features & Specifications

### Questionnaire Forms

**Essential Tier (12 fields):**
1. Race name (dropdown or custom)
2. Race website (optional URL)
3. Upload race docs (PDF/image, max 10MB)
4. Race date (date picker)
5. Goal finish time (HH:MM format)
6. Ultras completed (0, 1-3, 4-10, 10+)
7. Recent flat pace (MM:SS per mile)
8. Climbing strength (Strong/Average/Struggle)
9. Weekly training volume (miles)
10. Crew support (Yes/Partial/No)
11. Email (pre-filled from auth)
12. First name (pre-filled from auth)

**Custom Tier (+7 additional fields):**
13. Connect Strava (OAuth, analyze 90 days)
14. Recent race results (textarea, 500 char)
15. Biggest climb trained (text)
16. GI issues history (yes/no + details)
17. Blister-prone areas (text)
18. Nutrition preferences (checkboxes: vegan, gluten-free, caffeine-sensitive)
19. Biggest race fears (textarea, 300 char)

### 8-Step AI Agent Cascade

**Total Generation Time:** <5 minutes  
**OpenAI Cost:** ~$0.50-1.00 per guide

1. **Race Overview (45s)** - Course description, elevation profile, aid stations, historical weather
2. **Pacing Strategy (60s)** - Strava-based, elevation-adjusted, section-by-section pacing
3. **Cutoff Management (30s)** - Buffer calculator with 🟢🟡🔴 status indicators
4. **Crew Logistics (45s)** - Predicted arrival times, crew instructions per station
5. **Drop Bag Strategy (30s)** - Station-specific packing lists, weather adjustments
6. **Nutrition Timeline (30s)** - Personalized fueling plan, calorie/electrolyte targets
7. **Contingency Protocols (45s)** - GI issues, blisters, falling behind, heat protocols
8. **Mental Strategy (30s)** - Mantras, tough section tactics, motivation strategies

### API Endpoints

```typescript
// Authentication (Better Auth)
POST   /api/auth/signup
POST   /api/auth/login
GET    /api/auth/session
GET    /api/auth/google

// Payments (Polar.sh)
POST   /api/webhooks/polar

// Questionnaire
POST   /api/questionnaire       // Submit questionnaire
GET    /api/questionnaire/[id]  // Retrieve by ID
PUT    /api/questionnaire/[id]  // Update (auto-save)

// Strava Integration
GET    /api/strava/authorize    // OAuth flow
GET    /api/strava/callback     // OAuth callback
POST   /api/strava/analyze      // Analyze fitness data

// Guide Generation
POST   /api/generate-guide      // Trigger AI cascade
  // Request: { questionnaireId: uuid }
  // Response: { guideId, pdfUrl, generationTime }

// User Dashboard
GET    /api/guides              // List user's guides
GET    /api/guides/[id]         // Get specific guide
GET    /api/guides/[id]/download // Download PDF
```

## Development Guidelines

### Code Standards
- **TypeScript:** Use strict mode, no `any` types
- **Components:** React Server Components by default
- **Styling:** Tailwind utility classes only (no custom CSS)
- **Validation:** Zod schemas for all forms and API inputs
- **Error Handling:** Try-catch with proper error messages
- **Database:** Type-safe Drizzle queries, no raw SQL

### File Structure Conventions
```
app/
├── (auth)/              # Auth pages (login, signup)
├── (marketing)/         # Public pages (landing, pricing)
├── dashboard/           # Protected user dashboard
│   ├── _components/     # Dashboard-specific components
│   ├── guides/          # Guide listing & download
│   └── questionnaire/   # Questionnaire forms
└── api/                 # API routes

components/
├── ui/                  # shadcn/ui components
└── shared/              # Reusable app components

lib/
├── auth/                # Better Auth config
├── db/                  # Drizzle schema & connection
└── utils/               # Helper functions
```

### Component Patterns
- Use Server Components for data fetching
- Use Client Components only when needed (forms, interactivity)
- Mark client components with `'use client'` directive
- Co-locate components with routes when possible
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)

### Database Patterns
- Always use Drizzle ORM (type-safe)
- Use transactions for multi-table operations
- Index foreign keys and frequently queried fields
- Store JSON data in `jsonb` columns (Strava data, guide sections)

### API Design
- RESTful conventions (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Return proper HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 401, 404, 500)
- Validate inputs with Zod before processing
- Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
- Log errors to console for debugging

## 90-Day Development Roadmap

### Phase 1: Manual MVP (Weeks 1-4)
**Goal:** Validate demand with 30-50 manual guides

- [ ] Landing page (Next.js + Tailwind)
- [ ] Pricing page (3 tiers)
- [ ] Polar.sh payment integration
- [ ] Google Forms questionnaire (temporary)
- [ ] Manual guide generation (Claude prompts)
- [ ] Email delivery (Resend)
- [ ] First 5 beta testers

**Success:** 30-50 guides sold, <5% refund, 8+/10 satisfaction

### Phase 2: AI Automation (Weeks 5-12)
**Goal:** Automate guide generation, scale to 100 guides

- [ ] Better Auth setup (email + Google OAuth)
- [ ] Neon database + Drizzle migrations
- [ ] Questionnaire web forms (Essential + Custom)
- [ ] Strava OAuth integration
- [ ] 8-step AI cascade (OpenAI)
- [ ] Puppeteer PDF generation
- [ ] Cloudflare R2 storage
- [ ] User dashboard
- [ ] Email automation

**Success:** 100 automated guides, <5 min generation, zero failures

### Phase 3: Scale & Optimize (Months 4-6)
**Goal:** Scale to 500 guides, $50K revenue

- [ ] Weather integration
- [ ] Plan version updates
- [ ] Ultra Bundle management
- [ ] Referral program
- [ ] Race database expansion (50+ races)
- [ ] Admin dashboard
- [ ] A/B testing (landing page, pricing)
- [ ] SEO content

**Success:** 500 guides, $50K revenue, 15% repeat purchase

## Performance Requirements

| Metric | Target | Tool |
|--------|--------|------|
| Landing page load | <3 seconds | Vercel Analytics |
| Guide generation | <5 minutes | Custom logs |
| PDF generation | <30 seconds | Puppeteer timing |
| Database queries | <100ms | Drizzle logging |
| API response | <500ms | Vercel Edge |
| Uptime | 99.5% | Vercel status |

## Security Requirements

- Better Auth handles session management (database-backed)
- Strava OAuth tokens encrypted in database
- Polar.sh handles payment processing (PCI DSS compliant)
- HTTPS enforced by Vercel (automatic SSL)
- Rate limiting on API routes (Vercel middleware)
- Input validation with Zod on all forms
- CORS configuration for API security

## Brand Voice & Messaging

### Personality
- **Calm expert:** Never panicked, never hyped
- **Tactically specific:** Numbers, details, exact instructions
- **Data-forward but human-centered:** Tech serves humans

### Key Messages
- **Tagline:** "Stop piecing together advice. Start executing with confidence."
- **Value Prop:** "30 hours DIY planning → 10 minutes AI-generated guide"
- **Positioning:** "TrainingPeaks gets you fit. RaceWise gets you finished."

### Voice Examples
✅ **Good:** "At mile 62, slow your pace by 30 seconds/mile for the next 5 miles, eat 200 calories, take two salt tabs."

❌ **Bad:** "Believe in yourself! You got this! CRUSH your race!"

## Before Starting Any Feature

1. **Check PRD:** Read relevant section in `/docs/PRD_COMPLETE.md`
2. **Verify Tech Stack:** Use Neon (not Supabase), Better Auth (not NextAuth)
3. **Follow Schema:** Database structure is documented in PRD Section 3
4. **Reference Starter Kit:** Use existing patterns from the starter kit
5. **Ask Clarifying Questions:** If PRD is unclear, ask before building

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

❌ **Don't** use Supabase (we use Neon)
❌ **Don't** use NextAuth (we use Better Auth)
❌ **Don't** use Stripe (we use Polar.sh)
❌ **Don't** write custom CSS (use Tailwind only)
❌ **Don't** use `any` type (use proper TypeScript types)
❌ **Don't** bypass Drizzle ORM (no raw SQL queries)
❌ **Don't** ignore error handling (always try-catch)

